WEBVTT

1
00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:00.840
(HORSE WHINNIES)

2
00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:07.840
(MEN SHOUTING)

3
00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:17.280
NED: Does ser Hugh have any family
in the capital?

4
00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:19.000
No.

5
00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:23.640
I stood vigil for him myself last night.

6
00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:25.880
He had no one else.

7
00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:28.560
He'd never worn this armor before.

8
00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:30.960
Bad luck for him--

9
00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:33.240
going against the Mountain.

10
00:02:33.400 --> 00:02:35.600
Who determines the draw?

11
00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:37.680
All the knights draw straws. Lord Stark.

12
00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:39.560
Aye.

13
00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:41.640
But who holds the straws?

14
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:45.960
You've done good work. sisters.

15
00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:52.200
Life is strange.

16
00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:55.680
Not so many years ago
we fought as enemies at the Trident.

17
00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:58.800
I'm glad we never met on the field.
ser Barristan.

18
00:02:58.960 --> 00:03:01.640
As is my wife. I don't think
the widow's life would suit her.

19
00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.960
(CHUCKLES)
You're too modest.

20
00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:06.520
I've seen you cut down
a dozen great knights.

21
00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:10.000
My father once told me
you were the best he'd ever seen.

22
00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:13.040
I never knew the man to be wrong
about matters of combat.

23
00:03:13.200 --> 00:03:16.200
He was a fine man. your father.

24
00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:18.200
What the Mad King did to him
was a terrible crime.

25
00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:20.120
And that lad--

26
00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:21.800
he was a squire until a few months ago.

27
00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:24.800
How could he afford a new suit of armor?

28
00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:27.160
Perhaps Lord Arryn left him some money?

29
00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:32.120
-I hear the king wants to joust today.
-Yes. that will never happen.

30
00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:35.080
(CHUCKLES)
Robert tends to do what he wants.

31
00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:37.560
If the king got what he wanted
all the time.

32
00:03:37.720 --> 00:03:40.840
he'd still be fighting
a damned rebellion.

33
00:03:44.920 --> 00:03:47.920
It's made too small. your grace.
It won't go.

34
00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:52.160
Your mother was a dumb whore
with a fat ass. Did you know that?

35
00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:57.960
Look at this idiot!
One ball and no brains.

36
00:03:58.120 --> 00:04:00.800
He can't even put a man's armor
on him properly.

37
00:04:00.960 --> 00:04:02.400
You're too fat for your armor.

38
00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:06.080
Fat? Fat. is it?

39
00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:08.920
Is that how you speak to your king?

40
00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:14.200
(LAUGHING)

41
00:04:16.040 --> 00:04:18.200
That was funny. is it?

42
00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:20.840
No. your grace.

43
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:24.200
No? You don't like the Hand's joke?

44
00:04:24.360 --> 00:04:26.640
You're torturing the poor boy.

45
00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:29.280
You heard the Hand.
The king's too fat for his armor.

46
00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:33.680
Go find the breastplate stretcher-- now!

47
00:04:35.360 --> 00:04:37.320
"The breastplate stretcher"?

48
00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:40.000
How long before he figures it out?

49
00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:42.600
-Maybe you should have one invented.
-All right. all right.

50
00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:45.600
But you watch me out there--
I still know how to point a lance.

51
00:04:45.760 --> 00:04:48.200
You have no business jousting.
Leave that for the young men.

52
00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:51.560
Why. because I'm king? Piss on that.
I want to hit somebody!

53
00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:53.720
-And who's going to hit you back?
-Anybody who can.

54
00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:56.600
-And the last man in his saddle--
-Will be you.

55
00:04:56.760 --> 00:05:00.880
There's not a man in the Seven Kingdoms
would risk hurting you.

56
00:05:01.040 --> 00:05:03.240
Are you telling me those cowards
would let me win?

57
00:05:03.400 --> 00:05:05.720
Aye.

58
00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:12.520
-Drink.
-I'm not thirsty.

59
00:05:12.680 --> 00:05:14.800
Drink. Your king commands it.

60
00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:20.360
Gods.

61
00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.720
too fat for my armor.

62
00:05:23.880 --> 00:05:26.240
Your squire... A Lannister boy?

63
00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:28.760
Mm. A bloody idiot.

64
00:05:28.920 --> 00:05:30.720
but Cersei insisted.

65
00:05:31.760 --> 00:05:34.120
I have Jon Arryn to thank for her.

66
00:05:34.280 --> 00:05:37.080
"Cersei Lannister will make
a good match." he told me.

67
00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:39.640
"You'll need her father on your side."

68
00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:46.280
I thought being king meant
I could do whatever I wanted.

69
00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:50.320
Enough of this. Let's go watch 'em ride.

70
00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:52.960
At least I can smell
someone else's blood.

71
00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:55.600
-Robert?
-What?

72
00:05:55.760 --> 00:05:58.520
Oh.
(LAUGHS)

73
00:05:58.680 --> 00:06:01.240
An inspiring sight for the people. eh?

74
00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.080
Come. bow before your king!
Bow. you shits!

75
00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:07.160
(POLITE LAUGHTER)

76
00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:09.880
(CHEERING)

77
00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:20.320
-Where's Arya?
-At her dancing lessons.

78
00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:25.800
The Knight of the Flowers.

79
00:06:31.480 --> 00:06:34.040
Thank you. ser Loras.

80
00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:44.800
(NEIGHS)

81
00:06:53.320 --> 00:06:56.040
(HORSE FUSSING)

82
00:07:03.200 --> 00:07:05.720
Don't let ser Gregor hurt him.

83
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:08.360
-Hey.
-I can't watch.

84
00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:14.280
-100 gold dragons on the Mountain.
-I'll take that bet.

85
00:07:14.440 --> 00:07:17.000
Now what will I buy
with 100 gold dragons?

86
00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:20.120
A dozen barrels of Dornish wine?
Or a girl

87
00:07:20.280 --> 00:07:23.320
-from the pleasure houses of Lys?
-Or you could even buy a friend.

88
00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:27.720
-He's going to die.
-Ser Loras rides well.

89
00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.080
(NEIGHING)

90
00:07:35.880 --> 00:07:39.760
(FANFARE)

91
00:07:51.200 --> 00:07:52.720
(CROWD GASPS. MAN LAUGHS)

92
00:07:56.920 --> 00:07:58.680
Such a shame. Littlefinger.

93
00:07:58.840 --> 00:08:02.000
It would have been so nice for you
to have a friend.

94
00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:03.880
And tell me. lord Renly.

95
00:08:04.040 --> 00:08:07.480
when will you be having your friend?

96
00:08:07.640 --> 00:08:10.480
(NEIGHS)

97
00:08:16.840 --> 00:08:19.840
Loras knew his mare was in heat.
Quite crafty. really.

98
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.280
Ser Loras would never do that.

99
00:08:22.440 --> 00:08:27.080
-There's no honor in tricks.
-No honor and quite a bit of gold.

100
00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:30.080
(HELMET CLANKS)
Sword!

101
00:08:39.240 --> 00:08:41.080
(HORSE NEIGHS)

102
00:08:43.600 --> 00:08:45.760
(CROWD GASPS. HORSE NEIGHS)

103
00:08:48.360 --> 00:08:50.880
(CROWD GASPS. KNIGHT GRUNTS)

104
00:08:54.800 --> 00:08:56.640
Leave him be!

105
00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:06.880
(GROWLS)

106
00:09:16.920 --> 00:09:20.920
Stop this madness
in the name of your king!

107
00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:27.680
ROBERT: Let him go!

108
00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:37.960
I owe you my life. ser.

109
00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:40.600
I'm no ser.

110
00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:44.520
(CHEERING)

111
00:10:02.840 --> 00:10:04.360
Remove his hood.

112
00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:07.960
MARILLION:
# On that eve. the captive imp #

113
00:10:08.120 --> 00:10:10.840
# Downwards from his horse did limp #

114
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:15.760
# No more would he preen and primp
In garb of red and gold #

115
00:10:15.920 --> 00:10:18.400
TYRION: This isn't the Kingsroad.
You said we were riding for Winterfell.

116
00:10:18.560 --> 00:10:20.680
I did... Often and loudly.

117
00:10:20.840 --> 00:10:22.960
Very wise.

118
00:10:23.120 --> 00:10:24.600
They'll be out in droves.

119
00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:26.680
looking for me in the wrong place.

120
00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:29.560
Word's probably gotten to my father
by now.

121
00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:32.120
He'll be offering a handsome reward.

122
00:10:32.280 --> 00:10:35.280
Everyone knows
a Lannister always pays his debts.

123
00:10:35.440 --> 00:10:37.720
Would you be so good as to untie me?

124
00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:40.720
-And why would I do that?
-Why not?

125
00:10:40.880 --> 00:10:42.240
Am I going to run?

126
00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:44.320
The hill tribes would kill me
for my boots.

127
00:10:44.480 --> 00:10:45.920
Unless a shadowcat ate me first.

128
00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:50.040
Shadowcats and hill tribes
are the least of your concerns.

129
00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:53.400
Ah. the Eastern Road.

130
00:10:53.560 --> 00:10:55.400
We're going to the Vale.

131
00:10:55.560 --> 00:10:57.000
You're taking me to your sister's

132
00:10:57.160 --> 00:10:59.080
to answer for my imagined crimes.

133
00:10:59.240 --> 00:11:02.960
Tell me. Lady Stark. when was
the last time you saw your sister?

134
00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:06.640
-Five years ago.
-She's changed.

135
00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:10.120
She was always a bit touched. but now--
you might as well kill me here.

136
00:11:10.280 --> 00:11:14.320
-I am not a murderer. Lannister.
-Neither am I! I had nothing to do

137
00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:16.160
-with the attempt on your son's life.
-The dagger found--

138
00:11:16.320 --> 00:11:19.280
What sort of imbecile
arms an assassin with his own blade?

139
00:11:19.440 --> 00:11:21.400
-Should I gag him?
-Why?

140
00:11:21.560 --> 00:11:23.320
Am I starting to make sense?

141
00:11:23.480 --> 00:11:25.560
(THUDS. GRUNTS)

142
00:11:25.720 --> 00:11:27.800
CATELYN: Rodrik!
(SCREAMING)

143
00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:31.280
My lady. this way.

144
00:11:47.400 --> 00:11:50.720
Untie me.
If I die. what's the point?

145
00:11:55.320 --> 00:11:57.320
(NEIGHS)

146
00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:06.560
(SCREAMS)

147
00:12:38.280 --> 00:12:40.720
(HEAVY BREATHING)

148
00:12:40.880 --> 00:12:43.520
-Rodrik?
-I'll be fine. my lady.

149
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:47.400
There's no need to bloody yourself.

150
00:12:47.560 --> 00:12:49.720
Your first?

151
00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:52.880
You need a woman.

152
00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:55.000
Nothing like a woman after a fight.

153
00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:58.920
I'm willing if she is.

154
00:12:59.080 --> 00:13:02.000
(LAUGHING)

155
00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:14.560
-Bran.
-BRAN: The Iron Islands.

156
00:13:14.720 --> 00:13:16.520
Sigil: a kraken.

157
00:13:16.680 --> 00:13:18.680
Words: "We do not sow."

158
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:20.800
-Lords?
-The Greyjoys.

159
00:13:20.960 --> 00:13:22.320
Famed for their skills at archery.

160
00:13:22.480 --> 00:13:25.680
navigation and lovemaking.
(LAUGHS)

161
00:13:25.840 --> 00:13:27.800
And failed rebellions.

162
00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:31.240
Sigil: a stag--

163
00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:33.960
A crowned stag now that Robert's king.

164
00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:36.960
-Good.
-Words: "Ours is the fury."

165
00:13:37.120 --> 00:13:39.560
-Lords: the Baratheons.
-Mm-hmm.

166
00:13:39.720 --> 00:13:41.480
The Westerlands.

167
00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:43.440
-Sigil: a lion.
-Mmm.

168
00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:45.960
-Words: "A Lannister
always pays his debts."

169
00:13:46.120 --> 00:13:50.600
No. A common saying.
but not their official motto.

170
00:13:50.760 --> 00:13:53.800
-Lords: the Lannisters.
-We're still on their words.

171
00:13:53.960 --> 00:13:56.800
-I don't know them.
-You do know them. Think.

172
00:13:56.960 --> 00:13:59.400
"Unbowed. unbent. unbroken."

173
00:13:59.560 --> 00:14:01.520
-That's house Martell.
-"Righteous in wrath."

174
00:14:01.680 --> 00:14:05.440
-House Hornwood.
-"Family. duty. honor."

175
00:14:05.600 --> 00:14:07.240
Those are Tully words-- your mother's.

176
00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:10.880
-Are we playing a game?
-"Family. duty. honor"...

177
00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:12.840
-Is that the right order?
-You know it is.

178
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:15.840
Family comes first?

179
00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:19.400
Your mother had to leave Winterfell
to protect the family.

180
00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:21.840
How can she protect the family

181
00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:25.200
if she's not with her family?

182
00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:27.480
Your mother sat by your bed

183
00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.120
for three weeks while you slept--

184
00:14:30.280 --> 00:14:32.800
And then she left!

185
00:14:34.240 --> 00:14:38.120
When you were born. I was the one
who pulled you from your mother.

186
00:14:38.280 --> 00:14:40.640
I placed you in her arms.

187
00:14:40.800 --> 00:14:45.320
From that moment
until the moment she dies.

188
00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:47.840
she will love you.

189
00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.560
Absolutely.

190
00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:53.640
-Fiercely.
-Why did she leave?

191
00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:55.480
(SIGHS)
I still can't tell you.

192
00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:59.000
-but she will be home soon.
-Do you know where she is now?

193
00:14:59.160 --> 00:15:00.760
-Today?
-No. I don't.

194
00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:04.240
Then how can you promise me
she'll be home soon?

195
00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:10.280
Sometimes I worry you're too smart
for your own good.

196
00:15:10.440 --> 00:15:12.840
I'll never shoot another arrow.

197
00:15:14.160 --> 00:15:16.240
And where is that written?

198
00:15:16.400 --> 00:15:18.800
-You need legs to work a bow.
-Hmm.

199
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:21.360
If the saddle Lord Tyrion designed
actually works.

200
00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.840
you could learn to shoot a bow
from horseback.

201
00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:25.600
Really?

202
00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:29.000
Dothraki boys learn
when they're four years old.

203
00:15:29.160 --> 00:15:31.280
Why shouldn't you?

204
00:15:35.160 --> 00:15:37.120
(GRUNTING)

205
00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:45.120
(MOANS)

206
00:15:45.280 --> 00:15:47.520
Shh. keep it down.

207
00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:50.000
You're not supposed to be
inside the castle walls.

208
00:15:50.160 --> 00:15:53.240
I thought you were supposed to be
an important person around here.

209
00:15:53.400 --> 00:15:56.400
Important enough for the likes of you.

210
00:15:56.560 --> 00:15:58.880
You're not the only nobleman in my life.
you know.

211
00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:00.480
Who. the imp?

212
00:16:00.640 --> 00:16:02.280
I'd call him half a nobleman.

213
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:04.160
Jealous?

214
00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:06.040
Why should I be jealous?

215
00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:09.640
Anyone with a few coppers in his pocket
can own you for the night.

216
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:12.040
What's a dwarf like down below?

217
00:16:12.200 --> 00:16:13.800
I've always wondered.

218
00:16:13.960 --> 00:16:17.160
-Might surprise you.
-Hmm?

219
00:16:17.320 --> 00:16:19.840
He's good with his fingers too.

220
00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:22.200
And his tongue.

221
00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:24.160
Generous tipper.

222
00:16:24.320 --> 00:16:26.840
I guess gold is cheap for a Lannister.

223
00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:28.840
You are jealous.

224
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.520
I'm a Greyjoy.

225
00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:32.520
We've been lords of the Iron Islands
for 300 years.

226
00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:35.520
There's not a family in Westeros
that can look down on us.

227
00:16:35.680 --> 00:16:37.640
not even the Lannisters.

228
00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:39.400
And what about the Starks?

229
00:16:41.160 --> 00:16:43.520
I've been Lord Stark's ward
since I was eight years old.

230
00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:46.880
A ward-- that's a nice word for it.

231
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:49.680
Your father rebelled against king Robert
and if he does it again--

232
00:16:49.840 --> 00:16:52.880
My father fought
for the freedom of his people.

233
00:16:53.040 --> 00:16:56.520
What did your father do?
Fucked a cook and whelped a whore.

234
00:16:56.680 --> 00:16:59.200
You're a very serious boy.

235
00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:02.120
-I'm not a boy.
-Oh yes. you are.

236
00:17:02.280 --> 00:17:06.960
A serious boy with a serious cock.

237
00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:09.120
I don't want to pay for it.

238
00:17:09.280 --> 00:17:11.920
Then get yourself a wife.

239
00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:17.200
ARYA: Come on.
(MEOWS)

240
00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:20.680
I'm not gonna hurt you.
(MEOWS)

241
00:17:25.520 --> 00:17:26.840
(MEOWS)

242
00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:30.760
How is your son. my lord?

243
00:17:30.920 --> 00:17:33.600
He'll never walk again.

244
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:37.320
But his mind is sound?

245
00:17:37.480 --> 00:17:39.440
So they say.

246
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.560
A blessing then.

247
00:17:42.560 --> 00:17:45.640
I suffered an early mutilation myself.

248
00:17:47.440 --> 00:17:49.840
Some doors close forever...

249
00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:55.160
others open
in the most unexpected places.

250
00:17:55.320 --> 00:17:57.080
May I?

251
00:18:01.240 --> 00:18:04.040
If the wrong ears heard
what I'm about to tell you.

252
00:18:04.200 --> 00:18:06.160
off comes my head.

253
00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:08.120
And who would mourn poor Varys then?

254
00:18:08.280 --> 00:18:13.120
North or South.
they sing no songs for spiders.

255
00:18:13.280 --> 00:18:15.280
But there are things you must know.

256
00:18:15.440 --> 00:18:17.720
You are the King's Hand
and the king is a fool--

257
00:18:17.880 --> 00:18:19.880
your friend. I know. but a fool--

258
00:18:20.040 --> 00:18:22.760
and doomed unless you save him.

259
00:18:22.920 --> 00:18:25.080
I've been in the capital a month.

260
00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:29.040
Why have you waited so long
to tell me this?

261
00:18:29.200 --> 00:18:30.880
I didn't trust you.

262
00:18:31.040 --> 00:18:33.160
So why do you trust me now?

263
00:18:34.160 --> 00:18:37.920
The queen is not the only one
who has been watching you closely.

264
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:40.120
There are few men of honor
in the capital.

265
00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:41.840
You are one of them.

266
00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:43.480
I would like to believe I am another.

267
00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:45.640
strange as that may seem.

268
00:18:45.800 --> 00:18:48.320
What sort of doom does the king face?

269
00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:50.960
The same sort as Jon Arryn.

270
00:18:52.680 --> 00:18:54.880
The Tears of Lys. they call it.

271
00:18:55.040 --> 00:18:57.280
A rare and costly thing.

272
00:18:57.440 --> 00:19:01.600
as clear and tasteless as water.
It leaves no trace.

273
00:19:09.720 --> 00:19:11.400
Who gave it to him?

274
00:19:11.560 --> 00:19:15.800
Some dear friend. no doubt.
But which one? There were many.

275
00:19:15.960 --> 00:19:19.320
Lord Arryn was a kind and trusting man.

276
00:19:19.480 --> 00:19:24.160
There was one boy.
All he was he owed to Jon Arryn.

277
00:19:24.320 --> 00:19:26.960
The squire. ser Hugh?

278
00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:30.120
Pity what happened to him.

279
00:19:30.280 --> 00:19:33.120
just when his life
seemed to be going so nicely.

280
00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:37.280
If ser Hugh poisoned him--

281
00:19:38.560 --> 00:19:39.880
who paid ser Hugh?

282
00:19:41.600 --> 00:19:43.080
Someone who could afford it.

283
00:19:43.240 --> 00:19:45.960
Jon was a man of peace.

284
00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:49.400
He was Hand for 17 years--
17 good years.

285
00:19:49.560 --> 00:19:51.200
Why kill him?

286
00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:55.280
He started asking questions.

287
00:19:55.440 --> 00:19:58.280
(RUNNING FOOTSTEPS)

288
00:20:00.720 --> 00:20:02.120
(MEOWS)

289
00:20:22.840 --> 00:20:25.880
MAN'S VOICE:
He's found one bastard already.

290
00:20:26.040 --> 00:20:27.600
He has the book.

291
00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:29.480
The rest will come.
(LOCK CLICKS)

292
00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:31.760
MAN #2: And when he knows the truth.
what will he do?

293
00:20:31.920 --> 00:20:33.600
MAN #1: The gods alone know.

294
00:20:33.760 --> 00:20:36.560
The fools tried to kill his son.

295
00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:39.720
What's worse-- they botched it.

296
00:20:41.840 --> 00:20:44.920
The wolf and the lion
will be at each other's throats.

297
00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:48.080
-We will be at war soon. my friend.
-What good is war now?

298
00:20:48.240 --> 00:20:50.120
We're not ready.

299
00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:52.640
If one Hand can die. why not a second?

300
00:20:52.800 --> 00:20:55.360
This Hand is not the other.

301
00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:56.920
We need time.

302
00:20:57.080 --> 00:21:00.000
Khal Drogo will not make his move
until his son is born.

303
00:21:00.160 --> 00:21:01.520
You know how these savages are.

304
00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:05.320
"Delay." you say. "Move fast." I reply.

305
00:21:05.480 --> 00:21:08.720
This is no longer
a game for two players.

306
00:21:08.880 --> 00:21:10.600
It never was.

307
00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:32.640
The first to arrive
and the last to leave.

308
00:21:33.760 --> 00:21:35.800
I admire your industry.

309
00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:37.880
You do move quietly.

310
00:21:38.040 --> 00:21:40.960
We all have our qualities.

311
00:21:42.240 --> 00:21:43.880
You look a bit lonely today.

312
00:21:44.040 --> 00:21:47.600
You should pay a visit to my brothel
this evening. First boy is on the house.

313
00:21:47.760 --> 00:21:49.840
I think you're mistaking business
with pleasure.

314
00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:51.520
Am I?

315
00:21:53.240 --> 00:21:55.000
All those birds
that whisper in your ear--

316
00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:57.040
such pretty little things.

317
00:21:58.440 --> 00:22:00.560
Trust me.

318
00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:03.960
we accommodate all inclinations.

319
00:22:04.120 --> 00:22:08.080
Oh. I'm sure. Lord Redwyne
likes his boys very young. I hear.

320
00:22:08.240 --> 00:22:11.400
I'm a purveyor
of beauty and discretion--

321
00:22:11.560 --> 00:22:12.880
both equally important.

322
00:22:13.040 --> 00:22:17.360
Though I suppose beauty
is a subjective quality. no?

323
00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:21.400
Is it true that ser Marlon
of Tumblestone prefers amputees?

324
00:22:21.560 --> 00:22:24.560
All desires are valid
to a man with a full purse.

325
00:22:24.720 --> 00:22:27.880
And I heard the most awful rumor
about a certain lord

326
00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:29.880
with a taste for fresh cadavers.

327
00:22:30.040 --> 00:22:34.080
Must be enormously difficult
to accommodate that inclination.

328
00:22:34.240 --> 00:22:36.040
The logistics alone--

329
00:22:36.200 --> 00:22:38.640
to find beautiful corpses
before they rot.

330
00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:41.240
Strictly speaking. such a thing

331
00:22:41.400 --> 00:22:43.320
would not be
in accordance with the king's laws.

332
00:22:43.480 --> 00:22:45.640
Strictly speaking.

333
00:22:48.560 --> 00:22:50.720
Tell me-- does someone somewhere

334
00:22:50.880 --> 00:22:54.120
keep your balls in a little box?

335
00:22:54.280 --> 00:22:56.480
I've often wondered.

336
00:22:57.920 --> 00:22:59.440
Do you know I have no idea
where they are?

337
00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:03.160
And we had been so close.
(CHUCKLES)

338
00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:05.000
But enough about me. How have you been

339
00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:06.960
since we last saw each other?

340
00:23:07.120 --> 00:23:09.680
Since you last saw me
or since I last saw you?

341
00:23:09.840 --> 00:23:12.960
Now the last time I saw you. you
were talking to the Hand of the King.

342
00:23:13.120 --> 00:23:15.720
-Saw me with your own eyes?
-Eyes I own.

343
00:23:15.880 --> 00:23:17.360
Council business.

344
00:23:17.520 --> 00:23:20.320
We all have so much to discuss
with Ned Stark.

345
00:23:20.480 --> 00:23:23.600
Everyone's well aware
of your enduring fondness

346
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:26.040
for Lord Stark's wife.

347
00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:29.480
If the Lannisters were behind
the attempt on the Stark boy's life

348
00:23:29.640 --> 00:23:34.680
and it was discovered that you helped
the Starks come to that conclusion...

349
00:23:34.840 --> 00:23:37.760
To think a simple word to the queen--

350
00:23:37.920 --> 00:23:40.040
-One shudders at the thought.
-Ooh.

351
00:23:40.200 --> 00:23:42.680
But you know something?
I do believe that I have seen you

352
00:23:42.840 --> 00:23:44.480
even more recently
than you have seen me.

353
00:23:44.640 --> 00:23:47.240
-Have you?
-Yes.

354
00:23:47.400 --> 00:23:49.160
Earlier today. I distinctly recall

355
00:23:49.320 --> 00:23:51.400
seeing you talking to Lord Stark
in his chambers.

356
00:23:51.560 --> 00:23:53.520
Was that you under the bed?

357
00:23:53.680 --> 00:23:55.320
And not long after that

358
00:23:55.480 --> 00:23:58.640
is when I saw you escorting a certain

359
00:23:58.800 --> 00:24:01.120
foreign dignitary...

360
00:24:01.280 --> 00:24:03.600
Council business?

361
00:24:03.760 --> 00:24:06.760
Of course you would have friends
from across the Narrow Sea.

362
00:24:06.920 --> 00:24:09.360
You're from there yourself. after all.

363
00:24:09.520 --> 00:24:12.400
We're friends. aren't we. Lord Varys?

364
00:24:12.560 --> 00:24:14.640
I'd like to think we are.

365
00:24:14.800 --> 00:24:16.960
So you can imagine my burden.

366
00:24:17.120 --> 00:24:20.600
wondering if the king might question
my friend's sympathies.

367
00:24:20.760 --> 00:24:24.480
To stand at a crossroads where turning
left means loyalty to a friend.

368
00:24:24.640 --> 00:24:26.360
turning right. loyalty to the realm--

369
00:24:26.520 --> 00:24:28.920
-Oh. please.
-To find myself in a position

370
00:24:29.080 --> 00:24:30.640
where a simple word to the king--
(DOOR OPENS)

371
00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:33.680
What are you two conspiring about?

372
00:24:33.840 --> 00:24:36.600
Well. whatever it is.
you'd best hurry up.

373
00:24:36.760 --> 00:24:39.120
-My brother is coming.
-To a small council meeting?

374
00:24:39.280 --> 00:24:41.920
Disturbing news from far away.

375
00:24:43.520 --> 00:24:45.400
Haven't you heard?

376
00:24:46.520 --> 00:24:49.600
(BIRDS CAWING. WAVES BREAKING)

377
00:25:13.480 --> 00:25:15.200
Off with you. No begging.

378
00:25:15.360 --> 00:25:17.120
I'm not a beggar. I live here.

379
00:25:17.280 --> 00:25:19.320
D'you want a smack on your ear
to help you with your hearing?

380
00:25:19.480 --> 00:25:21.200
I want to see my father.

381
00:25:21.360 --> 00:25:23.880
I want to fuck the queen.
for all the good it does me.

382
00:25:24.040 --> 00:25:25.680
You want your father. boy?

383
00:25:25.840 --> 00:25:27.960
He's lying on the floor of some tavern.

384
00:25:28.120 --> 00:25:29.720
getting pissed on by his friends.

385
00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:31.440
My father is Hand of the King!

386
00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:34.680
I'm not a boy.
I'm Arya Stark of Winterfell

387
00:25:34.840 --> 00:25:38.040
and if you lay a hand on me. my father
will have both your heads on spikes.

388
00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:41.000
Now are you going to let me by
or do I need to smack you on the ear

389
00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:43.200
to help with your hearing?

390
00:25:45.120 --> 00:25:48.120
You know I had half my guard
out searching for you?

391
00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:54.400
-You promised me this would stop.
-They said they were going to kill you.

392
00:25:54.560 --> 00:25:57.080
-Who did?
-I didn't see them.

393
00:25:57.240 --> 00:25:58.960
-but I think one was fat.
-Oh. Arya.

394
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:01.560
I'm not lying!
They said you found the bastard

395
00:26:01.720 --> 00:26:04.440
and the wolves are fighting
the lions and the savage--

396
00:26:04.600 --> 00:26:06.200
something about the savage.

397
00:26:06.360 --> 00:26:08.560
-Where did you hear this?
-In the dungeons.

398
00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:11.600
-near the dragon skulls.
-What were you doing in the dungeons?

399
00:26:13.160 --> 00:26:14.760
Chasing a cat.

400
00:26:14.920 --> 00:26:17.200
(KNOCKS. DOOR OPENS)

401
00:26:17.360 --> 00:26:20.480
Pardon. my lord. There's a Night's
Watchman here begging a word.

402
00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:22.440
He says it's urgent.

403
00:26:28.680 --> 00:26:32.240
-Your name. friend?
-Yoren. if it please.

404
00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:34.840
-This must be your son. He has the look.
-I'm a girl!

405
00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:36.440
Did Benjen send you?

406
00:26:36.600 --> 00:26:38.320
No one sent me. my lord.

407
00:26:38.480 --> 00:26:40.840
I'm here to find men for the wall.

408
00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:44.320
see if there's any scum in the dungeons
that might be fit for service.

409
00:26:44.480 --> 00:26:45.840
Oh. we'll find recruits for you.

410
00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:49.240
Thank you. my lord.
But that's not why I disturb you now.

411
00:26:50.600 --> 00:26:53.240
Your brother Benjen.
his blood runs black--

412
00:26:53.400 --> 00:26:55.240
makes him as much my brother as yours.

413
00:26:56.560 --> 00:26:58.160
It's for his sake I rode here so hard

414
00:26:58.320 --> 00:27:00.640
I damn near killed my horse.

415
00:27:00.800 --> 00:27:02.280
There are others riding too.

416
00:27:02.440 --> 00:27:04.760
The whole city will know by tomorrow.

417
00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:07.280
Know what?

418
00:27:07.440 --> 00:27:09.720
Best said in private. my lord.

419
00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:18.040
Go on. We'll talk more later.

420
00:27:18.200 --> 00:27:21.000
Jory. take her safely to her room.

421
00:27:21.160 --> 00:27:23.440
Come along. my lady.
You heard your father.

422
00:27:29.280 --> 00:27:30.840
How many guards does my father have?

423
00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:33.800
Here in King's Landing? 50.

424
00:27:33.960 --> 00:27:36.400
You wouldn't let anyone kill him.
would you?

425
00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:39.120
No fear on that count. little lady.

426
00:27:43.720 --> 00:27:46.720
-Well?
-It's about your wife. my lord.

427
00:27:48.720 --> 00:27:50.440
She's taken the imp.

428
00:28:00.880 --> 00:28:02.600
(NEIGHS)

429
00:28:06.440 --> 00:28:08.240
You're far from home. Lady Stark.

430
00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:09.960
To whom do I speak?

431
00:28:10.120 --> 00:28:12.760
Ser Vardis Egan. Knight of the Vale.

432
00:28:12.920 --> 00:28:14.640
Is Lady Arryn expecting your visit?

433
00:28:14.800 --> 00:28:16.760
There was no time to send word.

434
00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:20.760
May I ask. my lady. why he is with you?

435
00:28:20.920 --> 00:28:23.480
That's why there was no time.

436
00:28:23.640 --> 00:28:25.680
-He is my prisoner.
-He doesn't look like a prisoner.

437
00:28:25.840 --> 00:28:29.760
My sister will decide
what he looks like.

438
00:28:29.920 --> 00:28:32.760
Yes. my lady. She will at that.

439
00:28:38.800 --> 00:28:41.920
The Eyrie. They say it's impregnable.

440
00:28:43.200 --> 00:28:45.560
Give me 10 good men
and some climbing spikes--

441
00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:48.480
I'll impregnate the bitch.

442
00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:50.760
TYRION: I like you.

443
00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:01.960
Lord Stark.
your presence has been requested

444
00:29:02.120 --> 00:29:04.080
in the small council chamber.
A meeting has been called.

445
00:29:04.240 --> 00:29:06.400
I need to see the king first-- alone.

446
00:29:06.560 --> 00:29:08.640
The king is
at the small council meeting. my lord.

447
00:29:08.800 --> 00:29:10.560
He has summoned you.

448
00:29:10.720 --> 00:29:13.520
-Is it about my wife?
-No. my lord.

449
00:29:13.680 --> 00:29:16.200
I believe it concerns
Daenerys Targaryen.

450
00:29:16.360 --> 00:29:18.760
The whore is pregnant.

451
00:29:18.920 --> 00:29:21.960
-You're speaking of murdering a child.
-I warned you this would happen.

452
00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:24.040
Back in the North. I warned you.

453
00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:28.480
but you didn't care to hear.
Well. hear it now.

454
00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:31.160
I want 'em dead. mother and child both.

455
00:29:31.320 --> 00:29:35.120
And that fool Viserys as well.
Is that plain enough for you?

456
00:29:35.280 --> 00:29:36.600
I want them both dead.

457
00:29:36.760 --> 00:29:39.120
You will dishonor yourself forever
if you do this.

458
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:42.560
Honor?!
I've got Seven Kingdoms to rule!

459
00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:45.680
One king. Seven Kingdoms.

460
00:29:45.840 --> 00:29:48.000
Do you think honor keeps them in line?

461
00:29:48.160 --> 00:29:50.120
Do you think
it's honor that's keeping the peace?

462
00:29:50.280 --> 00:29:52.680
It's fear-- fear and blood.

463
00:29:52.840 --> 00:29:54.400
Then we're no better than the Mad King.

464
00:29:54.560 --> 00:29:56.360
Careful. Ned. Careful now.

465
00:29:56.520 --> 00:29:58.480
You want to assassinate a girl

466
00:29:58.640 --> 00:30:00.240
because the Spider heard a rumor?

467
00:30:00.400 --> 00:30:03.040
No rumor. my lord.
The princess is with child.

468
00:30:03.200 --> 00:30:06.320
-Based on whose information?
-Ser Jorah Mormont.

469
00:30:06.480 --> 00:30:08.560
He is serving
as advisor to the Targaryens.

470
00:30:08.720 --> 00:30:10.840
Mormont? You bring us the whispers

471
00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:14.520
of a traitor half a world away
and call it fact?

472
00:30:14.680 --> 00:30:17.240
Jorah Mormont's a slaver. not a traitor.

473
00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:19.600
Small difference. I know.
to an honorable man.

474
00:30:19.760 --> 00:30:23.120
He broke the law. betrayed his family.
fled our land.

475
00:30:23.280 --> 00:30:25.200
We commit murder
on the word of this man?

476
00:30:25.360 --> 00:30:28.800
And if he's right? If she has a son?

477
00:30:28.960 --> 00:30:32.160
A Targaryen at the head
of a Dothraki army...

478
00:30:32.320 --> 00:30:36.120
-What then?
-The Narrow Sea still lies between us.

479
00:30:36.280 --> 00:30:39.960
I'll fear the Dothraki the day they
teach their horses to run on water.

480
00:30:40.120 --> 00:30:41.880
Do nothing?

481
00:30:42.040 --> 00:30:44.120
That's your wise advice?

482
00:30:44.280 --> 00:30:47.760
Do nothing till our enemies
are on our shores?

483
00:30:47.920 --> 00:30:49.840
You're my council. Counsel!

484
00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:53.480
Speak sense to this honorable fool.

485
00:30:53.640 --> 00:30:58.280
I understand your misgivings. my lord.
Truly. I do.

486
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:02.000
It is a terrible thing we must consider.
a vile thing.

487
00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:06.320
Yet we who presume to rule
must sometimes do vile things

488
00:31:06.480 --> 00:31:08.560
for the good of the realm.

489
00:31:08.720 --> 00:31:11.840
Should the gods grant Daenerys a son.

490
00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:13.360
the realm will bleed.

491
00:31:13.520 --> 00:31:15.440
I bear this girl no ill will.

492
00:31:15.600 --> 00:31:17.440
but should the Dothraki invade.

493
00:31:17.600 --> 00:31:19.320
how many innocents will die?

494
00:31:19.480 --> 00:31:21.360
How many towns will burn?

495
00:31:21.520 --> 00:31:24.960
Is it not wiser. kinder even.

496
00:31:25.120 --> 00:31:26.840
that she should die now

497
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:30.120
so that tens of thousands might live?

498
00:31:30.280 --> 00:31:32.680
We should have had them both killed
years ago.

499
00:31:32.840 --> 00:31:35.000
When you find yourself
in bed with an ugly woman.

500
00:31:35.160 --> 00:31:38.120
best close your eyes. get it over with.

501
00:31:38.280 --> 00:31:41.240
Cut her throat. Be done with it.

502
00:31:47.480 --> 00:31:49.920
I followed you into war--

503
00:31:50.080 --> 00:31:52.320
twice.

504
00:31:52.480 --> 00:31:54.000
without doubts.

505
00:31:54.160 --> 00:31:56.480
without second thoughts.

506
00:31:56.640 --> 00:31:59.880
But I will not follow you now.

507
00:32:00.040 --> 00:32:01.640
The Robert I grew up with

508
00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:05.720
didn't tremble
at the shadow of an unborn child.

509
00:32:07.200 --> 00:32:08.640
She dies.

510
00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:11.960
I will have no part in it.

511
00:32:12.120 --> 00:32:14.160
You're the King's Hand. Lord Stark.

512
00:32:14.320 --> 00:32:17.520
You'll do as I command
or I'll find me a Hand who will.

513
00:32:26.120 --> 00:32:28.280
And good luck to him.

514
00:32:28.440 --> 00:32:29.800
I thought you were a better man.

515
00:32:29.960 --> 00:32:32.000
Out. Out. damn you.

516
00:32:32.160 --> 00:32:34.720
I'm done with you.

517
00:32:34.880 --> 00:32:37.680
Go. run back to Winterfell!

518
00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:41.360
I'll have your head on a spike!

519
00:32:41.520 --> 00:32:44.280
ROBERT: I'll put it there myself.
you fool!

520
00:32:44.440 --> 00:32:47.720
You think you're too good for this?
Too proud and honorable?

521
00:32:47.880 --> 00:32:49.200
This is a war!

522
00:32:51.920 --> 00:32:53.280
I'll go ahead with my daughters.

523
00:32:53.440 --> 00:32:54.800
Get them ready. Do it yourself.

524
00:32:54.960 --> 00:32:57.520
-Don't ask anyone for help.
-Right away. my lord.

525
00:32:57.680 --> 00:33:00.080
Lord Baelish is here for you.

526
00:33:01.400 --> 00:33:03.680
His grace went on about you
at some length

527
00:33:03.840 --> 00:33:05.760
after you took your leave.

528
00:33:05.920 --> 00:33:07.360
The word "treason" was mentioned.

529
00:33:09.000 --> 00:33:11.880
-What can I do for you?
-When do you return to Winterfell?

530
00:33:12.040 --> 00:33:15.040
-Why? What do you care?
-If you're still here come nightfall.

531
00:33:15.200 --> 00:33:18.160
I'll take you to see the last person
Jon Arryn spoke with before falling ill.

532
00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:21.960
If that sort of thing
still interests you.

533
00:33:22.120 --> 00:33:23.720
I don't have the time.

534
00:33:23.880 --> 00:33:26.960
It won't take more than an hour.
But as you please.

535
00:33:32.040 --> 00:33:35.800
Round up all the men we have and station
them outside the girls' chambers.

536
00:33:35.960 --> 00:33:38.520
-Who are your best two swords?
-Heward and Wyl.

537
00:33:38.680 --> 00:33:41.560
Find them and meet me at the stables.

538
00:33:46.360 --> 00:33:48.680
You bring him here without permission?

539
00:33:48.840 --> 00:33:51.560
You pollute my home with his presence?

540
00:33:51.720 --> 00:33:54.400
(SUCKLING)

541
00:33:54.560 --> 00:33:56.200
Your aunt has done a bad thing. Robin.

542
00:33:56.360 --> 00:33:58.640
a very bad thing.

543
00:33:58.800 --> 00:34:01.480
You remember her. don't you?

544
00:34:01.640 --> 00:34:03.320
Isn't he beautiful?

545
00:34:03.480 --> 00:34:06.480
And strong too. Jon knew it.

546
00:34:06.640 --> 00:34:09.320
His last words were.
"The seed is strong."

547
00:34:09.480 --> 00:34:11.880
He wanted everyone to know
what a good. strong boy

548
00:34:12.040 --> 00:34:14.200
his son would grow up to be.

549
00:34:14.360 --> 00:34:17.480
Look at him. the lord of all the Vale.

550
00:34:17.640 --> 00:34:19.800
Lysa.

551
00:34:19.960 --> 00:34:22.120
you wrote me about the Lannisters.

552
00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:24.960
-warning me--
-To stay away from them!

553
00:34:25.120 --> 00:34:27.760
Not to bring one here!

554
00:34:27.920 --> 00:34:29.960
Mommy?

555
00:34:30.120 --> 00:34:32.520
-Is that the bad man?
-It is.

556
00:34:32.680 --> 00:34:35.000
(CREEPY LAUGH)

557
00:34:35.160 --> 00:34:37.280
He's little.

558
00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:40.560
LYSA: He's Tyrion.
the imp of house Lannister.

559
00:34:40.720 --> 00:34:43.280
He killed your father.
He murdered the Hand of the King!

560
00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:45.760
Oh. did I kill him too?

561
00:34:45.920 --> 00:34:47.560
I've been a very busy man.

562
00:34:47.720 --> 00:34:50.920
You will watch your tongue!

563
00:34:51.080 --> 00:34:52.720
These men are knights of the Vale.

564
00:34:52.880 --> 00:34:55.360
Every one of them loved Jon Arryn.

565
00:34:55.520 --> 00:34:57.240
Every one of them would die for me.

566
00:34:57.400 --> 00:35:00.720
If any harm comes to me.
my brother Jaime will see that they do.

567
00:35:00.880 --> 00:35:03.120
You can't hurt us. No one can hurt us
here. Tell him. mommy!

568
00:35:03.280 --> 00:35:07.280
-Tell him!
-Shh shh shh. my sweet boy.

569
00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:10.000
He's just trying to frighten us.

570
00:35:10.160 --> 00:35:11.640
Lannisters are all liars.

571
00:35:11.800 --> 00:35:14.400
No one will hurt my baby.

572
00:35:14.560 --> 00:35:16.840
Mommy...

573
00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:19.440
I want to see the bad man fly.

574
00:35:21.560 --> 00:35:23.080
Perhaps you will. my little love.

575
00:35:23.240 --> 00:35:25.320
This man is my prisoner.

576
00:35:25.480 --> 00:35:28.080
I will not have him harmed.

577
00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:31.600
Ser Vardis.

578
00:35:31.760 --> 00:35:33.840
my sister's guest is weary.

579
00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:37.360
Take him down below so he can rest.

580
00:35:37.520 --> 00:35:40.240
Introduce him to Mord.

581
00:35:41.920 --> 00:35:44.040
You go sleep. dwarf man.
(LAUGHING)

582
00:35:44.200 --> 00:35:46.360
Sleep good. little dwarf man!

583
00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:51.000
(SLAMS. LOCK CLANKS)

584
00:35:59.120 --> 00:36:02.840
(WIND GUSTING)

585
00:36:20.120 --> 00:36:22.800
Lord Stark's lucky he still has a head.

586
00:36:22.960 --> 00:36:25.200
Robert will rant for a few days.
but he won't do anything.

587
00:36:25.360 --> 00:36:27.360
He adores the man.

588
00:36:27.520 --> 00:36:29.360
(SURPRISED)
You're jealous.

589
00:36:29.520 --> 00:36:32.040
-Are you sure this won't hurt?
-Only if I slip.

590
00:36:32.200 --> 00:36:35.840
(SCRAPING)

591
00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:39.320
-And you'd prefer me like this?
-Mm-hmm.

592
00:36:39.480 --> 00:36:41.680
If you want hairless.
maybe you should find a little boy.

593
00:36:41.840 --> 00:36:44.480
I want you.

594
00:36:44.640 --> 00:36:47.560
My brother thinks that anyone
who hasn't been to war isn't a man.

595
00:36:47.720 --> 00:36:51.080
He treats me as if I'm a spoiled child.

596
00:36:51.240 --> 00:36:54.080
Oh. and you're not?

597
00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:56.400
Loras Tyrell. the Knight of the Flowers?

598
00:36:56.560 --> 00:36:58.560
How many wars have you fought in?

599
00:36:58.720 --> 00:37:01.760
Oh. and how much did your father spend
on that armor of yours?

600
00:37:01.920 --> 00:37:03.560
Hold still.

601
00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:07.520
All I ever hear from Robert and Stannis
is how I'm not tough enough.

602
00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:09.520
how I squirm at the sight of blood--

603
00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:11.800
You did vomit when that boy's eye
was knocked out in the melee.

604
00:37:11.960 --> 00:37:14.160
His eye was dangling
out of the damn socket!

605
00:37:14.320 --> 00:37:16.240
He shouldn't have entered the melee
if he didn't know how to fight.

606
00:37:16.400 --> 00:37:19.520
Easy for you to say.
Not everyone is such a gifted swordsman.

607
00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:22.200
(GROANS) 
It's not a gift. No one gave it to me.

608
00:37:22.360 --> 00:37:24.080
I'm good because I work at it--

609
00:37:24.240 --> 00:37:26.720
every day of my life
since I could hold a stick.

610
00:37:26.880 --> 00:37:29.120
I could work at fighting
all day. every day.

611
00:37:29.280 --> 00:37:30.840
and still never be as good as you.

612
00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:33.160
Yes well. I guess we'll never know.

613
00:37:34.640 --> 00:37:39.800
(SIGHS)

614
00:37:42.840 --> 00:37:45.240
-Everywhere?
-Everywhere.

615
00:37:45.400 --> 00:37:47.480
So how did it end up?

616
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.040
The Targaryen girl will die?

617
00:37:49.200 --> 00:37:52.480
It needs to be done.
unpleasant as it is.

618
00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:54.480
Robert's rather tasteless about it.

619
00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:58.160
Every time he talks about killing her.
I swear the table rises six inches.

620
00:37:58.320 --> 00:38:00.800
It's a shame he can't muster
the same enthusiasm for his wife.

621
00:38:00.960 --> 00:38:03.280
He does have a deep.
abiding lust for her money.

622
00:38:03.440 --> 00:38:05.400
You have to give it to the Lannisters--

623
00:38:05.560 --> 00:38:07.400
they may be the most pompous.
ponderous cunts

624
00:38:07.560 --> 00:38:08.880
the gods ever suffered
to walk the world.

625
00:38:09.040 --> 00:38:11.720
but they do have
outrageous amounts of money.

626
00:38:12.880 --> 00:38:14.640
I have an outrageous amount of money.

627
00:38:14.800 --> 00:38:16.640
Not as much as the Lannisters.

628
00:38:16.800 --> 00:38:19.920
(CHUCKLES)
But a lot more than you.

629
00:38:20.080 --> 00:38:23.280
Robert's threatening
to take me hunting with him.

630
00:38:23.440 --> 00:38:25.320
Last time we were out there
for two weeks.

631
00:38:25.480 --> 00:38:27.560
Tramping through the trees in the rain.
day after day.

632
00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:30.760
all so he can stick his spear
into something's flesh.

633
00:38:30.920 --> 00:38:34.320
Oh. But Robert loves his killing.

634
00:38:34.480 --> 00:38:36.040
-And he's the king.
-Hmm.

635
00:38:36.200 --> 00:38:39.520
-How did that ever happen?
-Because he loves his killing.

636
00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:42.400
And he used to be good at it.

637
00:38:42.560 --> 00:38:44.760
Do you know who should be king?

638
00:38:44.920 --> 00:38:47.120
-Be serious.
-I am.

639
00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:49.280
My father could be your bank.

640
00:38:49.440 --> 00:38:52.600
I've never fought in a war before.
but I'd fight for you.

641
00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:54.600
-I'm fourth in line.
-And where was Robert

642
00:38:54.760 --> 00:38:56.960
in the line of royal succession?

643
00:38:57.120 --> 00:39:00.360
-Joffrey is a monster. Tommen is eight.
-Stannis?

644
00:39:00.520 --> 00:39:01.840
Stannis has the personality
of a lobster.

645
00:39:02.000 --> 00:39:05.640
He's still my older brother.
What are you doing?!

646
00:39:05.800 --> 00:39:07.120
-Look at it.
-You cut me.

647
00:39:07.280 --> 00:39:10.760
It's just blood. We've all got it in us.
Sometimes a little spills.

648
00:39:10.920 --> 00:39:14.040
If you become king.
you're going to see a lot of this.

649
00:39:14.200 --> 00:39:16.160
You need to get used to it.

650
00:39:16.320 --> 00:39:18.240
Go on. Look.

651
00:39:20.280 --> 00:39:22.160
People love you.

652
00:39:23.600 --> 00:39:25.480
They love to serve you
because you're kind to them.

653
00:39:25.640 --> 00:39:27.960
They want to be near you.

654
00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:33.720
You're willing to do
what needs to be done.

655
00:39:33.880 --> 00:39:36.160
but you don't gloat over it.

656
00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:38.880
You don't love killing.

657
00:39:40.960 --> 00:39:42.440
Where is it written that power

658
00:39:42.600 --> 00:39:45.200
is the sole province of the worst?

659
00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:47.160
That thrones are only made

660
00:39:47.320 --> 00:39:49.920
for the hated and the feared?

661
00:39:53.240 --> 00:39:56.720
You would be a wonderful king.

662
00:39:58.840 --> 00:40:01.280
(SUCKING NOISES)

663
00:40:12.400 --> 00:40:15.520
I'm sorry your marriage
to Ned Stark didn't work out.

664
00:40:15.680 --> 00:40:17.160
You seemed so good together.

665
00:40:17.320 --> 00:40:20.520
I'm glad I could do something
to make you happy.

666
00:40:23.640 --> 00:40:26.240
Without a Hand.
everything will fall to pieces.

667
00:40:26.400 --> 00:40:28.080
I suppose this is where you tell me

668
00:40:28.240 --> 00:40:30.840
to give the job to your brother Jaime.

669
00:40:31.000 --> 00:40:34.120
No. He's not serious enough.

670
00:40:35.480 --> 00:40:37.280
I'll say this for Ned Stark:

671
00:40:37.440 --> 00:40:39.400
he's serious enough.

672
00:40:39.560 --> 00:40:42.920
Was it really worth it?
Losing him this way?

673
00:40:43.080 --> 00:40:44.800
I don't know.

674
00:40:46.960 --> 00:40:49.640
But I do know this:

675
00:40:49.800 --> 00:40:54.960
if the Targaryen girl convinces
her Horselord husband to invade

676
00:40:55.120 --> 00:40:59.160
and the Dothraki horde
crosses the Narrow Sea...

677
00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:01.800
we won't be able to stop them.

678
00:41:01.960 --> 00:41:04.160
The Dothraki don't sail.
Every child knows that.

679
00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:07.440
They don't have discipline.
They don't have armor.

680
00:41:07.600 --> 00:41:10.840
-They don't have siege weapons.
-It's a neat little trick you do:

681
00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:13.840
you move your lips
and your father's voice comes out.

682
00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:17.760
(SCOFFS)
Is my father wrong?

683
00:41:20.440 --> 00:41:22.920
Let's say Viserys Targaryen lands

684
00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:26.480
with 40.000 Dothraki screamers
at his back.

685
00:41:26.640 --> 00:41:28.880
We hole up in our castles--

686
00:41:29.040 --> 00:41:30.560
a wise move--

687
00:41:30.720 --> 00:41:34.160
only a fool would meet the Dothraki
in an open field.

688
00:41:34.320 --> 00:41:37.080
They leave us in our castles.

689
00:41:37.240 --> 00:41:40.480
They go from town to town.
looting and burning.

690
00:41:40.640 --> 00:41:44.200
killing every man who can't hide
behind a stone wall.

691
00:41:44.360 --> 00:41:46.680
stealing all our crops and livestock.

692
00:41:46.840 --> 00:41:49.560
enslaving all our women and children.

693
00:41:49.720 --> 00:41:52.040
How long do the people
of the Seven Kingdoms stand behind

694
00:41:52.200 --> 00:41:55.240
their absentee king. their cowardly king

695
00:41:55.400 --> 00:41:57.760
hiding behind high walls?

696
00:41:57.920 --> 00:42:00.480
When do the people decide
that Viserys Targaryen

697
00:42:00.640 --> 00:42:02.880
is the rightful monarch after all?

698
00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:06.520
We still outnumber them.

699
00:42:07.920 --> 00:42:11.000
Which is the bigger number: five or one?

700
00:42:12.600 --> 00:42:14.400
Five.

701
00:42:14.560 --> 00:42:16.360
Five...

702
00:42:18.040 --> 00:42:20.000
One.

703
00:42:20.160 --> 00:42:22.200
One army-- a real army

704
00:42:22.360 --> 00:42:27.440
united behind one leader
with one purpose.

705
00:42:27.600 --> 00:42:31.480
Our purpose died with the Mad King.

706
00:42:31.640 --> 00:42:33.640
Now we've got as many armies

707
00:42:33.800 --> 00:42:37.720
as there are men
with gold in their purse.

708
00:42:37.880 --> 00:42:39.520
And everybody wants something different.

709
00:42:39.680 --> 00:42:41.760
Your father wants to own the world.

710
00:42:41.920 --> 00:42:44.920
Ned Stark wants to run away
and bury his head in the snow.

711
00:42:45.080 --> 00:42:46.400
What do you want?

712
00:42:56.680 --> 00:43:00.160
We haven't had a real fight
in nine years.

713
00:43:00.320 --> 00:43:02.280
Back-stabbing doesn't prepare you
for a fight.

714
00:43:02.440 --> 00:43:04.360
And that's all the realm is now:

715
00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:06.440
back-stabbing and scheming

716
00:43:06.600 --> 00:43:10.240
and arse-licking and money-grubbing.

717
00:43:10.400 --> 00:43:13.920
Sometimes I don't know
what holds it together.

718
00:43:14.080 --> 00:43:16.960
Our marriage.

719
00:43:25.040 --> 00:43:27.960
Ah. so here we sit

720
00:43:28.120 --> 00:43:30.400
17 years later.

721
00:43:30.560 --> 00:43:33.320
holding it all together.

722
00:43:33.480 --> 00:43:35.400
Don't you get tired?

723
00:43:35.560 --> 00:43:37.560
Every day.

724
00:43:39.160 --> 00:43:41.960
How long can hate hold a thing together?

725
00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:45.800
Well. 17 years is quite a long time.

726
00:43:46.840 --> 00:43:48.920
Yes. it is.

727
00:43:49.080 --> 00:43:50.600
Yes. it is.

728
00:43:55.960 --> 00:43:58.240
What was she like?

729
00:44:00.280 --> 00:44:02.320
You've never asked about her. not once.

730
00:44:02.480 --> 00:44:04.640
Why not?

731
00:44:04.800 --> 00:44:08.320
At first. just saying her name
even in private

732
00:44:08.480 --> 00:44:12.120
felt like I was breathing life
back into her.

733
00:44:12.280 --> 00:44:13.640
I thought if I didn't talk about her.

734
00:44:13.800 --> 00:44:16.160
she'd just fade away for you.

735
00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:19.000
When I realized
that wasn't going to happen.

736
00:44:19.160 --> 00:44:21.840
I refused to ask out of spite.

737
00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:23.840
I didn't want to give you
the satisfaction of thinking

738
00:44:24.000 --> 00:44:26.640
I cared enough to ask.

739
00:44:26.800 --> 00:44:29.760
And eventually it became clear that
my spite didn't mean anything to you.

740
00:44:29.920 --> 00:44:32.560
As far as I could tell.
you actually enjoyed it.

741
00:44:32.720 --> 00:44:34.560
So why now?

742
00:44:36.400 --> 00:44:40.560
What harm could Lyanna Stark's ghost
do to either of us

743
00:44:40.720 --> 00:44:43.440
that we haven't done to each other
a hundred times over?

744
00:44:47.120 --> 00:44:50.040
You want to know the horrible truth?

745
00:44:52.440 --> 00:44:55.640
I can't even remember
what she looked like.

746
00:44:57.760 --> 00:45:02.440
I only know she was the one thing
I ever wanted...

747
00:45:04.280 --> 00:45:07.760
Someone took her away from me.

748
00:45:07.920 --> 00:45:12.360
and Seven Kingdoms couldn't fill
the hole she left behind.

749
00:45:15.720 --> 00:45:17.880
I felt something for you once. you know?

750
00:45:19.280 --> 00:45:20.800
I know.

751
00:45:20.960 --> 00:45:23.920
Even after we lost our first boy.

752
00:45:25.680 --> 00:45:27.280
For quite a while. actually.

753
00:45:31.640 --> 00:45:33.080
Was it ever possible for us?

754
00:45:33.240 --> 00:45:36.280
Was there ever a time. ever a moment?

755
00:45:42.840 --> 00:45:44.800
No.

756
00:45:48.200 --> 00:45:51.040
Does that make you feel better or worse?

757
00:45:55.360 --> 00:45:57.520
It doesn't make me feel anything.

758
00:46:07.480 --> 00:46:10.120
(DOOR OPENS. CLOSES)

759
00:46:11.640 --> 00:46:15.240
She looks like him. don't she. my lord?

760
00:46:15.400 --> 00:46:20.640
-She has his nose. his black hair.
-Aye.

761
00:46:20.800 --> 00:46:22.600
Tell him when you see him. my lord.

762
00:46:22.760 --> 00:46:27.360
If it please you.
tell him how beautiful she is.

763
00:46:28.520 --> 00:46:31.920
-I will.
-Tell him I've been with no one else.

764
00:46:32.080 --> 00:46:35.320
I swear it. my lord.
by the old gods and new.

765
00:46:35.480 --> 00:46:37.440
I don't want no jewels or nothing.

766
00:46:37.600 --> 00:46:39.160
just him.

767
00:46:39.320 --> 00:46:40.920
The king was always good to me.

768
00:46:41.080 --> 00:46:44.840
When Jon Arryn came to visit you.
what did he want?

769
00:46:45.000 --> 00:46:47.200
He wasn't that sort of man. my lord.

770
00:46:47.360 --> 00:46:49.960
He just wanted to know
if the child was happy.

771
00:46:50.120 --> 00:46:51.920
healthy.

772
00:46:54.720 --> 00:46:56.760
She looks healthy enough to me.

773
00:46:58.480 --> 00:47:00.400
The girl shall want for nothing.

774
00:47:06.600 --> 00:47:10.160
Brothels make a much better investment
than ships. I've found.

775
00:47:10.320 --> 00:47:13.800
Whores rarely sink.

776
00:47:17.240 --> 00:47:19.520
What do you know
of king Robert's bastards?

777
00:47:19.680 --> 00:47:23.440
Well. he has more than you. for a start.

778
00:47:23.600 --> 00:47:25.480
-NED: How many?
-Does it matter?

779
00:47:25.640 --> 00:47:28.320
If you fuck enough women.
some of them will give you presents.

780
00:47:28.480 --> 00:47:30.320
And Jon Arryn tracked them all down.
Why?

781
00:47:30.480 --> 00:47:33.200
He was the King's Hand.
Perhaps Robert wanted them looked after.

782
00:47:33.360 --> 00:47:36.200
He was overcome with fatherly love.

783
00:47:39.520 --> 00:47:41.040
Come.

784
00:47:46.800 --> 00:47:48.720
-Jory!
-My lord.

785
00:48:07.080 --> 00:48:08.800
Such a small pack of wolves.

786
00:48:10.880 --> 00:48:12.640
Stay back. ser.
This is the Hand of the King.

787
00:48:12.800 --> 00:48:14.520
Was the Hand of the King.

788
00:48:14.680 --> 00:48:18.400
Now I'm not sure what he is--
lord of somewhere very far away.

789
00:48:18.560 --> 00:48:20.720
What's the meaning of this. Lannister?

790
00:48:20.880 --> 00:48:23.240
Get back inside where it's safe.

791
00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:24.880
I'm looking for my brother.

792
00:48:25.040 --> 00:48:26.680
You remember my brother.
don't you. Lord Stark?

793
00:48:26.840 --> 00:48:32.160
-Blond hair. sharp tongue. short man.
-I remember him well.

794
00:48:32.320 --> 00:48:35.040
It seems he had some trouble
on the road.

795
00:48:35.200 --> 00:48:37.600
You wouldn't know what happened to him.
would you?

796
00:48:37.760 --> 00:48:39.920
He was taken at my command

797
00:48:40.080 --> 00:48:41.800
to answer for his crimes.

798
00:48:41.960 --> 00:48:44.400
LITTLEFINGER: My lords!
(HORSE NEIGHS)

799
00:48:44.560 --> 00:48:47.120
I'll bring the City Watch.

800
00:48:48.640 --> 00:48:51.720
Come. Stark.
I'd rather you die sword in hand.

801
00:48:51.880 --> 00:48:54.120
-If you threaten my lord again--
-Threaten?

802
00:48:54.280 --> 00:48:57.000
As in. "I'm going to open your lord"

803
00:48:57.160 --> 00:49:00.480
"from balls to brains
and see what Starks are made of"?

804
00:49:00.640 --> 00:49:03.520
You kill me.

805
00:49:03.680 --> 00:49:05.840
your brother's a dead man.

806
00:49:06.000 --> 00:49:07.560
You're right.

807
00:49:07.720 --> 00:49:10.280
Take him alive. Kill his men.

808
00:49:12.360 --> 00:49:15.000
(SCREAMS)

809
00:50:16.080 --> 00:50:17.720
(GROANS)

810
00:50:41.720 --> 00:50:45.000
My brother. Lord Stark--
we want him back.

811
00:50:52.120 --> 00:50:55.280
(NEIGHS)
